  "prompt": "What are the best questions answered by novels?",
  "response": "Novels can explore and answer complex questions about human nature, society, and individual experiences. Here are some profound questions often addressed in great literature:\n\n1. Personal Identity and Growth\n- Who am I?\n- How do people change over time?\n- What shapes an individual's character?\n\n2. Moral Dilemmas\n- What is right and wrong?\n- How do people make difficult ethical choices?\n- Can good people do bad things?\n\n3. Relationships and Human Connection\n- What defines love?\n- How do relationships transform people?\n- What are the dynamics of human interaction?\n\n4. Social and Cultural Challenges\n- How do societal structures impact individual lives?\n- What are the effects of prejudice and discrimination?\n- How do people navigate complex social systems?\n\n5. Existential Questions\n- What is the meaning of life?\n- How do people find purpose?\n- How do humans cope with mortality?\n\n6. Psychological Exploration\n- What motivates human behavior?\n- How do past experiences shape present actions?\n- What are the depths of human emotion?\n\n7. Power and Conflict\n- How do people respond to oppression?\n- What are the mechanisms of power?\n- How do individuals resist or succumb to systemic challenges?\n\nEach novel offers unique insights into these universal questions.",
